  "prompt": "How much cubic meter of cement, sand required for 12mm cement sand plaster 1:6 for 950 sq m?",
  "response": "To calculate the amount of cement and sand required for a 12 mm thick cement-sand plaster at a mix ratio of 1:6 for an area of 950 square meters, you can follow these steps:\n\n### Step 1: Calculate the volume of plaster required\n\n1. **Area to be plastered**: 950 m\u00b2\n2. **Thickness of plaster**: 12 mm = 0.012 m\n\n**Volume of plaster** = Area \u00d7 Thickness\n\\[ \n\\text{Volume of plaster} = 950 \\, \\text{m}\u00b2 \\times 0.012 \\, \\text{m} = 11.4 \\, \\text{m}\u00b3 \n\\]\n\n### Step 2: Calculate the quantities of cement and sand\n\nThe mix ratio is 1:6 (1 part cement to 6 parts sand), making a total of 7 parts.\n\n1. **Total parts** = 1 (cement) + 6 (sand) = 7 parts\n\nNow, calculate the volumes of cement and sand based on the total volume of plaster:\n\n2. **Volume of cement**:\n\\[ \n\\text{Volume of cement} = \\left(\\frac{1}{7}\\right) \\times 11.4 \\, \\text{m}\u00b3 \\approx 1.63 \\, \\text{m}\u00b3 \n\\]\n\n3. **Volume of sand**:\n\\[ \n\\text{Volume of sand} = \\left(\\frac{6}{7}\\right) \\times 11.4 \\, \\text{m}\u00b3 \\approx 9.77 \\, \\text{m}\u00b3 \n\\]\n\n### Summary\n\n- **Cement required**: approximately **1.63 m\u00b3**\n- **Sand required**: approximately **9.77 m\u00b3**\n\nMake sure to adjust the calculations in line with any local material properties or specific moisture content and wastage factors that may influence the final quantities needed at the worksite.",
